name: r-fftw
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0-7" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fftw
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/fftw_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/fftw/fftw_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f69f63467b84e107f3e0b18d1f034a37140545e6f50e6be3b887df2b4eec3a1e

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}grep              # [win]
    - {{ posix }}autoconf
    - {{ posix }}automake          # [not win]
    - {{ posix }}automake-wrapper  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}pkg-config
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - fftw >=3
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - fftw >=3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('fftw')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('fftw')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=fftw
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  summary: Provides a simple and efficient wrapper around the fastest Fourier transform in the west (FFTW) library <http://www.fftw.org/>.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: fftw
# Version: 1.0-6
# Title: Fast FFT and DCT Based on the FFTW Library
